<br>
Now to something I do know what i'm talking about.<br>
<br>
Since i've gotten into my 50's i've begun to realize that in the end game AC doesn't mean much of anything once it's above 1000.  It's all about your HP.  So, i've begun to work on my sta a lot more.  For a monk it's very important to have enough hp to actually make it back to the party alive.  <br>
<br>
My current ranking of abilities for a high lvl Monk:<br>
<br>
1) level (smaller Agro radius = superior pulling)<br>
<br>
2) hp (lets you get smacked or nuked a few times on the way back)<br>
<br>
3) sta (heavy 2hb weapons drain monk sta bar fast, need at least 100 sta and more sta = more hp)<br>
<br>
4) AC (take less damage from being smacked and get hit less often)<br>
<br>
5) Agi (more agi = more dodge ,block, and misses)<br>
<br>
6) Str/Dex (Str is better unless you're using a weapon that procs)<br>
<br>
Most useless stats are int, wis, and cha.  none of these serve any purpose for a high lvl monk in anything except buying and selling from vendors.<br>
<br>
I didn't mentions resists because they are a flexible stat which vary on what dungeon you are pulling in.  It's good to keep a lot of resist gear on you/in the bank in case you need it.<br>
<br>
I'm basing this on being a member of a well rounded 50+ group. <p><center>
